The endogeneity bias of OLS is \(\gamma\alpha\sigma_U^2/\sigma_T^2\): the coefficient of \(T\) in the observational mean exceeds the causal coefficient \(\beta\) by this amount. Numerically, with \(\alpha = \gamma = 1\) and \(\sigma_U^2 = \sigma_\delta^2 = 1\): \[\text{bias} = \frac{1 \times 1 \times 1}{1^2 \times 1 + 1} = \frac{1}{2} = 0.5.\]


